  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the wood-fired oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Season the pork chops with salt and black pepper on both sides.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together minced garlic, chopped rosemary, and a squeeze of lemon juice.",
    "Rub the garlic-rosemary mixture evenly onto both sides of the pork chops.",
    "Drizzle the pork chops with olive oil and place them on the baking stone in the wood-fired oven.",
    "Bake for 15-20 minutes or until the internal temperature reaches 145°F (63°C).",
    "Brush the Canadian maple syrup on the pork chops during the last 2-3 minutes of baking (if using).",
    "Remove the pork chops from the oven and let them rest for 5 minutes before serving.",
    "Serve the pork chops hot, garnished with additional rosemary if desired."
